Phase 4 — Alerting Strategy
Avoid the trap of "alert on every metric." Alert on symptoms, not causes, and use multi-window burn rate alerting for SLO-based alerts:
# alerts/nexus-slo-alerts.yaml
groups:
  - name: nexus.slo.burnrate
    rules:
      # PAGE: Fast burn — losing budget too fast (1h window, 14x burn rate)
      # At this rate you burn 30d budget in ~51 hours
      - alert: NexusSLOBudgetBurnRateHigh
        expr: |
          (
            sli:nexus_composite:ratio_rate5m < (1 - 14 * (1 - 0.999))
          ) and (
            sli:nexus_composite:ratio_rate1h < (1 - 14 * (1 - 0.999))  
          )
        for: 2m
        labels:
          severity: critical
          team: platform
        annotations:
          summary: "Nexus burning error budget at 14x rate"
          description: >
            At current burn rate, 30-day error budget exhausted in 
            {{ $value | humanizeDuration }}. Immediate action required.
          runbook_url: "https://wiki.internal/runbooks/nexus-p1"

      # TICKET: Slow burn — will exhaust budget by month end  
      - alert: NexusSLOBudgetBurnRateMedium
        expr: |
          sli:nexus_composite:ratio_rate6h < (1 - 3 * (1 - 0.999))
        for: 15m
        labels:
          severity: warning
          team: platform
        annotations:
          summary: "Nexus error budget degrading (3x burn rate)"
